clinical_study.brief_title: Pharmacokinetic, Safety and Immunogenicity Phase I Study of HLX14 Versus Prolia® in Healthy Male Subjects
clinical_study.official_title: A Randomised, Parallel, Single-Dose, Subcutaneous Injection, Phase I Clinical Study Of HLX14 Versus Prolia® (Denosumab) In Chinese Healthy Adult Male Subjects For Comparison In Pharmacokinetic Characteristics, Safety, And Immunogenicity

brief_summary.textblock: This is a randomised, single-dose, subcutaneous injection, parallel study designed to compare the PK of HLX14 and EU-sourced Prolia® in healthy Chinese adult male subjects, and to assess the safety, tolerability, and immunogenicity of these 2 drugs.

primary_outcome.description: Area under the serum concentration-time curve from time 0 to the last concentration-quantifiable time t of denosumab
Maximum serum concentration following administration of denosumab
Area under the serum concentration-time curve from time 0 to infinity

secondary_outcome.description: Time to reach maximum serum concentration following administration
Area under the effect-time curve from time zero to last time of quantifiable concentration of Serum CTX1
Minimum observed plasma concentration of Serum CTX1
Maximum Percent Inhibition of Serum CTX1
Time to reach Imin of Serum CTX1

arm_group.description: HLX14 are given subcutaneous injection at a single dose of 60 mg.
EU-Prolia® are given subcutaneous injection at a single dose of 60 mg.
